This species is easily recognized from other bromeliad species by its almost completely black appearance. 
<taxonomicName id="F4FF5AF940325F19FE77F9484D423EB5" authorityName="Rotheray &amp; Hancock &amp; Marcos-García" authorityYear="2007" box="[389,550,1730,1751]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="304" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="otongaensis">
<emphasis id="018BFD6840325F19FE77F9484D423EB5" box="[389,550,1730,1751]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="304">C. otongaensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is also black, but among other characters that species has a very different facial profile (
<figureCitation id="ABC43DFF40325F19FE98F9754E833F77" box="[362,487,1791,1813]" captionStart="Figures 15–18" captionStartId="11.[162,252,1847,1866]" captionTargetBox="[186,1416,201,1808]" captionTargetId="figure-77@11.[178,1426,198,1814]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Figures 15–18. Adult Copestylum, lateral view of the head; scale line = 3.5 mm. 15. Copestylum joei sp. nov., male holotype; 16. Copestylum louisae sp. nov., male holotype; 17. Copestylum otongaensis sp. nov., male holotype; 18. Copestylum puyarum sp. nov., female holotype." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5429850" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5429850/files/figure.png" pageId="37" pageNumber="304">Figs 15, 17</figureCitation>
). Among 
<taxonomicName id="F4FF5AF940325F19FDA2F9754FA83F56" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="304" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="018BFD6840325F19FDA2F9754DB03F76" box="[592,724,1791,1812]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="304">Copestylum</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
in general 
<taxonomicName id="F4FF5AF940325F19FEABF8944EFA3F51" authorityName="Rotheray &amp; Hancock &amp; Marcos-García" authorityYear="2007" box="[345,414,1822,1843]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="304" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="joei">
<emphasis id="018BFD6840325F19FEABF8944EFA3F51" box="[345,414,1822,1843]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="304">C. joei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is most similar to 
<taxonomicName id="F4FF5AF940325F19FD77F8944EC53F30" authority="(Williston, 1887)" baseAuthorityName="Williston" baseAuthorityYear="1887" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="304" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="anna">
<emphasis id="018BFD6840325F19FD77F8944FB83F30" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="304">Copestylum anna</emphasis>
(Williston, 1887)
</taxonomicName>
, but differs from that species in having black, not orange, eye hairs and antennae, a broader less tapering face, and a lack of pruniose patches on the gena. The early stages of 
<taxonomicName id="F4FF5AF940325F19FAE7FF694A3D389B" authorityName="Rotheray &amp; Hancock &amp; Marcos-García" authorityYear="2007" box="[1301,1369,227,249]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="304" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="joei">
<emphasis id="018BFD6840325F19FAE7FF694A3D389B" box="[1301,1369,227,249]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="304">C. joei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
share with 
<taxonomicName id="F4FF5AF940325F19FC87FE884C863975" authorityName="Rotheray &amp; Hancock &amp; Marcos-García" authorityYear="2007" box="[885,994,258,279]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="304" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="louisae">
<emphasis id="018BFD6840325F19FC87FE884C863975" box="[885,994,258,279]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="304">C. louisae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="F4FF5AF940325F19FBEEFE884A6B3975" authorityName="Rotheray &amp; Hancock &amp; Marcos-García" authorityYear="2007" box="[1052,1295,258,279]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="304" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="puyarum">
<emphasis id="018BFD6840325F19FBEEFE884A6B3975" box="[1052,1295,258,279]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="304">Copestylum puyarum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
an extended posterior end, but the extension is much broader in 
<taxonomicName id="F4FF5AF940325F19FCC8FEB54C1B3937" authorityName="Rotheray &amp; Hancock &amp; Marcos-García" authorityYear="2007" box="[826,895,319,341]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="304" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="joei">
<emphasis id="018BFD6840325F19FCC8FEB54C1B3937" box="[826,895,319,341]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="304">C. joei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. It has transverse prolegs like 
<taxonomicName id="F4FF5AF940325F19FB1AFEB54A0A3937" authorityName="Rotheray &amp; Hancock &amp; Marcos-García" authorityYear="2007" box="[1256,1390,319,341]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="304" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="puyarum">
<emphasis id="018BFD6840325F19FB1AFEB54A0A3937" box="[1256,1390,319,341]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="304">C. puyarum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but in 
<taxonomicName id="F4FF5AF940325F19FCAEFED44CC53911" authorityName="Rotheray &amp; Hancock &amp; Marcos-García" authorityYear="2007" box="[860,929,350,371]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="304" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="joei">
<emphasis id="018BFD6840325F19FCAEFED44CC53911" box="[860,929,350,371]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="304">C. joei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
they are equally developed on all first six abdominal segments. 
<taxonomicName id="F4FF5AF940325F19FBC1FEF74BC539F3" authorityName="Rotheray &amp; Hancock &amp; Marcos-García" authorityYear="2007" box="[1075,1185,380,402]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="304" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="louisae">
<emphasis id="018BFD6840325F19FBC1FEF74BC539F3" box="[1075,1185,380,402]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="304">C. louisae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has spherical prolegs. The vestiture of the thorax is much shorter in 
<taxonomicName id="F4FF5AF940325F19FAAFFE114AC639D3" authorityName="Rotheray &amp; Hancock &amp; Marcos-García" authorityYear="2007" box="[1373,1442,411,433]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="304" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="joei">
<emphasis id="018BFD6840325F19FAAFFE114AC639D3" box="[1373,1442,411,433]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="304">C. joei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
than in 
<taxonomicName id="F4FF5AF940325F19FC68FE304B4439AD" authorityName="Rotheray &amp; Hancock &amp; Marcos-García" authorityYear="2007" box="[922,1056,442,463]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="304" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="puyarum">
<emphasis id="018BFD6840325F19FC68FE304B4439AD" box="[922,1056,442,463]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="304">C. puyarum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and none of the segmental sensilla are on long projections. The close approximation of lappets 1 and 2, which lie one above the other and share a common base, also separates 
<taxonomicName id="F4FF5AF940325F19FB2DFD9C4A473A49" authorityName="Rotheray &amp; Hancock &amp; Marcos-García" authorityYear="2007" box="[1247,1315,534,555]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="304" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="joei">
<emphasis id="018BFD6840325F19FB2DFD9C4A473A49" box="[1247,1315,534,555]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="304">C. joei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from other bromeliad 
<taxonomicName id="F4FF5AF940325F19FC47FDBE4B5D3A2B" authorityName="Macquart" authorityYear="1846" box="[949,1081,564,585]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="304" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="018BFD6840325F19FC47FDBE4B5D3A2B" box="[949,1081,564,585]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="304">Copestylum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3340217A40325F19FCC8FDE84B683AB6" blockId="37.[826,1442,610,724]" pageId="37" pageNumber="304">
<emphasis id="018BFD6840325F19FCC8FDE84CF13A15" box="[826,917,610,631]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="304">Biology:</emphasis>
A larva was collected in wet decaying leaves at the base of a dead flower spike of a puya plant (
<taxonomicName id="F4FF5AF940325F19FCB3FD2A4CB93AD4" box="[833,989,672,694]" class="Liliopsida" family="Bromeliaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="37" pageNumber="304" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Bromeliaceae</taxonomicName>
) in 
<collectingCountry id="4BE861EA40325F19FBE3FD2A4BF73AD4" box="[1041,1171,672,694]" name="Costa Rica" pageId="37" pageNumber="304">Costa Rica</collectingCountry>
. Larvae of 
<taxonomicName id="F4FF5AF940325F19FAEFFD2A4AC63AD7" authorityName="Rotheray &amp; Hancock &amp; Marcos-García" authorityYear="2007" box="[1309,1442,672,693]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="304" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="puyarum">
<emphasis id="018BFD6840325F19FAEFFD2A4AC63AD7" box="[1309,1442,672,693]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="304">C. puyarum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were also present.
</paragraph>
